POiO is released under three licenses, one per kind of material, because a
software license alone does not cleanly cover hardware design files or written
content. Copyright (c) 2026 Jaime Ortega.

  Software   — the skill, the engine, firmware, build scripts, and any source
               code in this repository.
               License: Apache License 2.0
               Full text: LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt

  Hardware   — physical design files: the Rhino model (hardware/*.3dm),
               schematics, PCB layouts, 3D-printable meshes (STL/STEP), BOMs,
               and mechanical drawings.
               License: CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 — Strongly
               Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S-2.0)
               Full text: LICENSES/CERN-OHL-S-2.0.txt

  Content    — written and creative material: documentation (README, the
               hardware plans), recipe data, the style guide, reference text,
               logos, and other assets.
               License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0
               International (CC-BY-SA-4.0)
               Full text: LICENSES/CC-BY-SA-4.0.txt

All three are reciprocal / share-alike: you are free to use, modify, and sell
POiO and works based on it, provided your derivatives stay open under the same
license and credit the original. Trademarks (the "POiO" name and logo) are not
licensed for use in a way that implies endorsement.

As the sole copyright holder, Jaime Ortega may also offer POiO under other terms;
the licenses above govern this public release only.

When the license for a particular file is ambiguous, the buckets above decide it:
source code is Apache-2.0, physical-design files are CERN-OHL-S-2.0, and
everything else (prose, data, assets) is CC-BY-SA-4.0.
